Tanzania Lowers Gasoline Price 2.1% to 2,070 Shillings

-- B y   D a v i d   M a l i n g h a   D o y a
-- 
2011-08-29T06:11:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/tanzania-cuts-gasoline-diesel-and-kerosene-prices-energy-authority-says.html
(Corrects retail prices in second paragraph.)  Tanzania reduced the price of
gasoline 2.1 percent as world prices decreased, the Energy and
Water Utilities Regulatory Authority said.  Gasoline will cost 2,070 shillings a liter starting today
for the next two weeks, the authority said in a statement on its
website today. Diesel prices were cut 1.6 percent to 1,999
shillings while kerosene was lowered 1.3 percent to 1,980
shillings.  To contact the reporter on this story:
David Malingha Doya in Johannesburg at 
 dmalingha@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  